THE new African Transformation Movement has promised to bring political killings to an end if the party wins the election. Party president Vuyolethu Zungula said Mzansi had become a murderous country where killers aren’t punished. “Our brothers and sisters are murdered for petty things like cellphones, and this can’t continue to ravage society anymore. “It’s better for the wealthy as they’re protected in secured estates, with private security companies assuring their safety behind high walls.” Zungola, addressing the media in Rivonia, Joburg, introduced the party’s premier candidates: